<br>
rand(30)<br>
mpoload (crappy necklace)<br>
say Thanks sucker!<br>
give scroll $n<br>
else<br>
rand(30)<br>
mpoload (fastcast ring vnum)<br>
say Thanks sucker!<br>
give scroll $n<br>
else<br>
rand(30)etc....<br>
else<br>
rand(15)<br>
mpoload (blade of walnan vnum)<br>
say Thanks sucker!<br>
give scroll $n<br>
else<br>
rand(5)<br>
mpoload (airpet vnum)<br>
say Thanks sucker!<br>
give scroll $n<br>
etc etc<br>
<br>
This is technically random but you must past the if-checks for all the others to even get to the good stuff.  So if you pass the first 6 or 7 if-checks with none of them passing, you get to the good/decent stuff and if you get past that you get to the pets.  I'll bet this is how its set up.<br>
<br>
It could be why so many people get the crap spells and not the useful ones anyways.<br>
